<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Questionable status. Reported from Greece by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kisseleva, M. I." journalOrPublisher="Thalassograhica" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="107 - 118" title="Comparative characteristics of the Benthos at some banks in the Aegean Sea" volume="6" year="1983">Kisseleva (1983)</bibRefCitation>
. In the Mediterranean also reported from Egypt (
<bibRefCitation author="Fauvel, Pierre" journalOrPublisher="Direction des Recherches des Pecheries, Notes et Memoires" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1 - 60" title="Les Fonds de Peches pres d'Alexandrie XI. Annelides Polychetes" volume="90" year="1937">Fauvel 1937</bibRefCitation>
) and Italy (
<bibRefCitation author="Castelli, A" journalOrPublisher="Biologia Marina Mediterranea" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="323 - 373" title="AnnelidaPolychaeta" volume="15" year="2008">Castelli et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
) but 
<bibRefCitation author="Nygren, Arne" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1 - 314" title="Revision of Autolytinae (Syllidae: Polychaeta)" volume="680" year="2004">Nygren (2004)</bibRefCitation>
restricts it to the Arctic, the North-West Atlantic and the North Pacific.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
